Project Manifesto: TaraDSP (High-Performance Mastering / IR Toolkit)
1. Project Overview
TaraDSP is a professional-grade, command-line driven audio utility specifically designed for the creation, processing, and management of Impulse Responses (IRs). Developed in Free Pascal, it bridges the gap between simple convolution scripts and high-end audio engineering software.
2. Core Architecture & Performance

    Engine: Powered by the PFFFT (Pretty Fast FFT) library, ensuring
    complexity for convolutions.
    Precision: All internal processing is performed in the 32-bit IEEE Float domain to maintain maximum dynamic range and prevent rounding errors.
    SIMD Optimization: Supports SSE/AVX2 instruction sets (via compiler flags) for lightning-fast batch processing of large IR libraries.

3. Professional Audio Features
3.1 Advanced DSP Suite

    Zero-Latency Alignment: Includes a Minimum Phase Transform (via Real Cepstrum) to align various IRs to Sample 0 while preserving frequency response.
    Surgical Shaping: Integrated Biquad Filters (High-Pass & Low-Pass) with Butterworth characteristics (12dB/octave).
    Dynamic Control: Automatic Peak Normalization, RMS-based Auto-Gain Compensation (AGC), and manual Gain adjustment in dB.
    Polarity & Time: Supports Phase Inversion (-p) and Time Inversion (Reverse Reverb effects).

3.2 Signal Integrity

    Dithering: High-quality TPDF (Triangular Probability Density Function) dither to eliminate quantization distortion.
    Noise Shaping: First-order High-Pass Error Diffusion to shift quantization noise into less audible frequency ranges when downsampling to 16-bit.
    Fading & Trimming: Sample-accurate Silence Trimming with a dB-threshold and adjustable Linear Fade-In/Out to prevent digital clicks.

4. Hardware & Software Compatibility

    Clean RIFF Export: Implements WAVE-Chunk-Stripping to produce "lean" files, ensuring 100% compatibility with hardware modelers (Helix, Kemper, Quad Cortex, etc.).
    Sampler Integration: Support for Loop-Point Tagging (smpl chunk) and MIDI Unity Note embedding.
    Metadata Branding: Professional branding via LIST INFO chunks (Title, Artist, Comment) for DAW and OS integration.
    Format Suite: Seamless conversion between 16-bit PCM, 24-bit PCM, and 32-bit IEEE Float.

5. Workflow & Automation

    Batch Processing: Automatically process entire directories with a single command.
    Configuration: Persistent settings via INI-file support, allowing for studio-wide default configurations (Author, Bit-Depth, etc.).
    Diagnostics: Detailed WAVE-Header Analysis and ASCII-Art Waveform Preview for instant visual feedback in the terminal.
    Logging: High-resolution performance monitoring via TStopwatch to track throughput and processing times.

